"Available resources are insuffi cient to assist all households, even if they all more or less require support. # GFD implementation 3.3 Targeting groups\nSocio-economic discrepancies are documented in the course of assessment -it may be diffi cult to ascertain their mere existence, and the exercise must be thorough and unbiased. In the absence of socio-economic discrepancies, all community members are considered to need aid (or not), and the issue is resolved. If disparities have been detected on the other hand, means must be found to identify the households that do require assistance by use of appropriate indicators. The second question then arises: is this feasible?"